<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>Email Verification</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
        }

        .container {
            width: 100%;
            max-width: 600px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            background-color: #ffffff;
            padding: 20px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }

        .header {
            text-align: center;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: space-between;
            padding: 10px 0;
            background-color: #4e91e9a2;
        }

        .header img {
            max-width: 100px;
        }

        .content {
            padding: 20px;
        }

        .content h1 {
            color: #333333;
        }

        .content p {
            color: #555555;
            line-height: 1.6;
        }

        .content .otp {
            font-size: 20px;
            color: #007bff;
            margin: 20px 0;
            font-weight: bold;
            display: inline-block;
            padding: 10px;
            border: 1px dashed #007bff;
            background-color: #f9f9f9;
        }

        .footer {
            text-align: center;
            padding: 10px 0;
            color: #999999;
            font-size: 12px;
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="header">
            <img src="../image/brand/logo.svg" alt="Company Logo">
            <h1 style="color:#064d4d">HealthLink</h1>
        </div>
        <div class="content">
            <h1>Hey {{FirstName}},</h1>
            <p>Please use the following OTP code to confirm your email:</p>
            <p class="otp">{{otp}}</p>
            <p>If you did not request this email, you can safely ignore it.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="footer">
            <p>Â© {{currentYear}}Your Company. All rights reserved.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>

</html>